1
00:00:53,845 --> 00:00:59,476
GYMNASIUM

2
00:00:59,559 --> 00:01:02,020
One, two, three. Here we go.

3
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:25,293
Being apart…

4
00:01:26,211 --> 00:01:28,213
was never an issue in a relationship.

5
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:30,173
I'm content with how it is.

6
00:01:30,256 --> 00:01:31,925
No way! They dance with girls?

7
00:01:32,008 --> 00:01:34,302
Oh, I wish I took this class.

8
00:01:34,385 --> 00:01:36,763
Check out the guys without partners.

9
00:01:36,846 --> 00:01:38,139
Poor little wallflowers.

10
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:40,100
They kind of remind me of you, really.

11
00:01:53,029 --> 00:01:54,572
I think he likes Na-bi.

12
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:58,284
I bet he'll ask her out
when classes are over.

13
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:00,286
-Let's go.
-Okay.

14
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:02,580
Come on.

15
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:08,586
Yay! We got it all right!
I did good, yeah? I did!

16
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:10,171
We're gonna get an A+ for sure. Right?

17
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,355
Pretty good dancer.

18
00:02:28,189 --> 00:02:30,900
-You saw?
-I passed by and watched.

19
00:02:33,444 --> 00:02:35,071
I knew you'd be good at it.

20
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:37,407
I'm just glad I didn't step
on my partner's feet.

21
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:40,368
-Thanks, though.
-That's all I get?

22
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:42,203
And a free meal.

23
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:44,080
Cool.

24
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:49,836
You stayed up again?

25
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:52,422
I think you're working yourself too--

26
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:54,757
Thanks to you, I'm changing that.

27
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:57,010
Remember you asked me to?

28
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:01,389
That was about dating, you idiot.

29
00:03:02,765 --> 00:03:05,018
Look, I tried applying lacquer on glass.

30
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:06,436
It didn't work.

31
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,813
It didn't stay on. It keeps slipping off.

32
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,483
-How do you fix that?
-Well, you know…

33
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,527
You'd have to roughen up
the surface first.

34
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:15,904
How do you know?

35
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:20,241
From my aunt, she does pottery.
I picked up a few things.

36
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:24,787
Well, I wanna learn, too.

37
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:27,165
I tried putting glaze on glass
and baking it.

38
00:03:27,248 --> 00:03:28,875
It changed colors every single time.

39
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:29,876
It was so cool.

40
00:03:31,794 --> 00:03:32,754
I can give you tips.

41
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:35,757
But I'm sure I'll always be better
than you at it.

42
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:40,887
Close enough to be with her,
yet keeping enough distance,

43
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:42,263
to not risk ever hurting her.

44
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:44,474
-You like that?
-No.

45
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:46,017
Is that bad?

46
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:48,978
Isn't it pretty?

47
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:58,196
EPISODE 6: THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS LOVE. NEVERTHELESS,

48
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:03,368
Listen, are you really just friends
with Jae-eon? Answer me.

49
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:07,288
Yeah. We're just friends.

50
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:08,915
That's a relief.

51
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:11,709
I was beginning to get worried
I said too much.

52
00:04:19,509 --> 00:04:22,262
You know what? Don't cut your hair.

53
00:04:22,845 --> 00:04:23,721
What?

54
00:04:24,305 --> 00:04:25,515
It's Jae-eon.

55
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:28,476
He likes doing it with your hair tied.

56
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:56,462
Everyone,
look at what I just gave you.

57
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:59,090
What you have
is a list of commonly used colors,

58
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:02,343
and the different images,
and keywords that people, through time,

59
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:04,637
have seemed to associate
with these colors.

60
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:06,264
In varying shades and hues.

61
00:05:07,265 --> 00:05:10,226
You may have noticed
that some colors are associated

62
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:12,395
with images that are total opposites.

63
00:05:13,271 --> 00:05:17,275
This can simply be explained
by the differences in culture or country.

64
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:21,738
And by each individual's preference
and experience.

65
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:23,114
Good job, everyone.

66
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:25,742
Thank you, sir!

67
00:05:26,242 --> 00:05:27,827
Finally it's over!

68
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:29,954
It's finally over!

69
00:05:30,038 --> 00:05:32,081
-So that's it?
-Hand me my bag.

70
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:35,877
Where is Na-bi? Has anyone seen her today?

71
00:05:36,794 --> 00:05:38,671
Na-bi? I haven't seen her today.

72
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:40,256
-Not me.
-Me, too.

73
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,550
-Have you?
-And no messages, too.

74
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:45,762
-Did she call you, Jae-eon?
-Mm.

75
00:05:45,845 --> 00:05:47,305
Did something happen to her?

76
00:05:47,388 --> 00:05:49,766
I'm trying to call her,
but she's not picking up.

77
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:52,101
I'm sure she's fine,
maybe she just skipped school.

78
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:54,228
-She's not you, Bit-na.
-What?

79
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:56,064
Well, we have to go.
Great job today, guys.

80
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:57,398
-See you tomorrow.
-Bye.

81
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:59,233
Hey, where are you going?
Where are you going?

82
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:01,194
-See ya!
-I'll buy you two bowls.

83
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:03,071
-I'll be back after lunch.
-Come on, Jin-su!

84
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:05,281
-Coming!
-How about some tteokbokki?

85
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:06,824
You up for tteokbokki?

86
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,327
-Sure.
-Great, did you bring your wallet?

87
00:06:10,244 --> 00:06:11,329
Yeah, my treat.

88
00:06:11,412 --> 00:06:12,872
Okay.

89
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:16,542
-Let's go.
-Let's go. Let's go.

90
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:24,318
NOODLE SHOP

91
00:07:54,849 --> 00:07:55,808
I'm worried.

92
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:58,936
About what?

93
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:01,814
It's Na-bi. I can't seem to reach her.

94
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:04,609
Really?

95
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:06,736
Well, she was probably shocked.

96
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:09,780
-What?
-Nothing.

97
00:08:09,864 --> 00:08:10,781
I think she's pretty.

98
00:08:11,657 --> 00:08:14,577
You only saw her for a minute,
and you felt that?

99
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,245
I can see why you fell for her.

100
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:17,872
What are you talking about?

101
00:08:19,415 --> 00:08:20,750
It isn't like that.

102
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:23,878
Chris and I broke up, by the way.

103
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:25,963
Why?

104
00:08:29,425 --> 00:08:31,969
Don't act like you don't know. Seriously?

105
00:08:34,222 --> 00:08:37,558
He said he thought he was okay
with me seeing other guys,

106
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:39,977
but, as it turns out, he really wasn't.

107
00:08:41,437 --> 00:08:44,273
But I think I know how that feels now.

108
00:08:45,107 --> 00:08:48,027
So that's it? You guys are over?

109
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:51,531
Mm-hm. I just had to let him go.

110
00:08:52,573 --> 00:08:53,658
I did the right thing.

111
00:08:57,286 --> 00:09:00,289
What? Isn't that what you've always hated?

112
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:02,875
Clingy girls all over you.

113
00:09:06,754 --> 00:09:09,382
Ms. Yun Seol-a,
could you follow me, please?

114
00:09:12,176 --> 00:09:13,886
You can go if you're busy.

115
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:15,638
I'm not. You go ahead.

116
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:32,697
WHERE ARE YOU?

117
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:36,701
YU NA-BI

118
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:45,960
The person you're trying
to reach is currently unavailable…

119
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,988
She just disappeared.

120
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:25,916
Thank you so much!

121
00:10:26,542 --> 00:10:27,835
Hi, Na-bi!

122
00:10:28,377 --> 00:10:30,588
Aunt Jeong-suk!

123
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:36,010
Oh, Na-bi, come here, dear.

124
00:10:37,094 --> 00:10:39,055
It's so nice to see you again.

125
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:42,892
-Can I ask for a favor?
-Mm?

126
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:45,603
Could you not tell my mom
that I'm here visiting?

127
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:47,605
Why, are you in trouble with the law?

128
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:51,359
No, it's nothing like that.

129
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:52,943
Well, it's fine, then.

130
00:10:53,694 --> 00:10:55,071
How long will you be staying?

131
00:10:55,154 --> 00:10:58,324
Maybe… a week?

132
00:10:58,407 --> 00:11:00,451
Oh? That long, huh?

133
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:04,580
What? Don't you want me around that long?

134
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,040
No, it's fine.

135
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,752
You know I can help out and do chores.

136
00:11:09,835 --> 00:11:14,090
All right. I guess we can do the chores
that I've been putting off for so long.

137
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:15,341
We'll finally get it done.

138
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:17,677
For sure. You can count on me.

139
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,470
Ooh?

140
00:11:28,562 --> 00:11:30,606
POTTERY WORKSHOP

141
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:35,820
This feels so great.

142
00:11:35,903 --> 00:11:38,739
-Nice weather's today, huh?
-Yeah, it is.

143
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:41,617
Oh, by the way,
I saw Do-hyeok at the market.

144
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:43,411
What a fine young man he is.

145
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:45,287
Didn't know he was still around.

146
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:47,957
I remember it so well.

147
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:50,501
Before you went back to Seoul
when you were little,

148
00:11:50,584 --> 00:11:54,380
all your friends came to see you off,
but Do-hyeok didn't come, did he?

149
00:11:54,463 --> 00:11:55,297
No, he didn't.

150
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:57,299
Never was a child so blue.

151
00:11:57,383 --> 00:12:00,094
You were just crying
and whining the entire trip.

152
00:12:00,177 --> 00:12:01,971
What? No. That isn't true.

153
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:05,307
Of course, it was, and expected,
since you two were very close.

154
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:08,185
Yeah, that's right.

155
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:11,021
I guess, I really did
like Do-hyeok back then.

156
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:13,983
-Maybe more than like.
-It wasn't like that, stop teasing!

157
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:16,235
-It's not what I saw.
-Stop it!

158
00:12:18,362 --> 00:12:21,574
-Oh, my, let me get that.
-No, it's okay, I got it.

159
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:25,161
-To the workshop first, right?
-Yes. Come on.

160
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:28,914
Let's go!

161
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:32,376
-Come down after you unpack.
-Yep, I will.

162
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:34,378
-See you later!
-I'll see you later.

163
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:24,303
You are so cute.

164
00:13:24,386 --> 00:13:26,639
-What's gotten into you?
-You are!

165
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:29,141
-We better eat.
-No.

166
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,561
-No!
-Hey, lunch time is almost over.

167
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:36,816
I wanted to ask you.

168
00:13:37,775 --> 00:13:39,985
Don't you think it's time
we tell the others about this?

169
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:42,029
-About what?
-About me and you.

170
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,991
Why? It's not like
we're getting married, dude.

171
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:47,952
But we're dating, and I want them to know.

172
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:49,787
Why keep it any longer?

173
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:51,247
Hmm…

174
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:54,375
No, I don't want to tell anyone yet.

175
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:56,335
Why don't you want to?

176
00:13:57,628 --> 00:14:00,589
'Cause they're not gonna quit
talking about us when they find out.

177
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:05,302
Okay. Let's stop arguing
and just keep making out, huh?

178
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:08,472
You're just trying to change the subject,
but it's not going to work.

179
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:11,100
-No one's here, come on!
-Hold on a second. Let go of me first.

180
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:12,643
What are you two doing here?

181
00:14:12,726 --> 00:14:14,728
We're having lunch!
What are you guys doing here?

182
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:16,814
Are you planning to make out
or something? Don't lie.

183
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:19,900
What are you talking about?
We're just friends, you know, platonic.

184
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:22,027
Wait. Let me ask you something.

185
00:14:22,778 --> 00:14:25,197
I heard from someone
that Ms. Jo and Mr. An were seen

186
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:27,908
coming out of a motel
somewhere together. Is that true?

187
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:31,078
Nope. Not a motel, rather a house.

188
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:33,455
What? They were together in a house?

189
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:35,958
-Mm-hm.
-Wait, are they living together?

190
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:38,002
Well, even if they weren't,
it definitely means

191
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:40,504
there's something going on with them,
dating at the very least.

192
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:42,673
-Ugh, that's gross.
-Why is that gross?

193
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:44,383
'Cause they're so not right
for each other!

194
00:14:44,466 --> 00:14:45,843
They're so different.

195
00:14:45,926 --> 00:14:46,969
Yeah, that's ridiculous.

196
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:48,804
That's why I don't want
to believe the rumors.

197
00:14:49,346 --> 00:14:52,558
But they… they spend
so much time together.

198
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:54,393
Maybe they just fell for each other.

199
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,741
YUN SOL

200
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:13,287
-Sol, hi.
-Hey, Na-bi!

201
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:15,497
-Why are you ignoring my calls, but…
-Hey!

202
00:15:16,332 --> 00:15:18,250
…but answered Sol's?

203
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:21,378
Hey, Ji-wan.

204
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:24,089
You coming to the workshop?
Everyone's going, even Sol.

205
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,552
Um, I don't think I can.

206
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:29,637
Why not?

207
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,639
I thought we changed
the location because of you.

208
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:33,432
What? To where?

209
00:15:33,515 --> 00:15:36,060
Yeah, you know the place
your noodle shop friend runs?

210
00:15:36,143 --> 00:15:37,478
The guest house.

211
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:39,480
-You're coming here?
-"Here"?

212
00:15:39,563 --> 00:15:41,398
Is that we're you're at right now?

213
00:15:42,691 --> 00:15:44,818
No, I'm not.

214
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:48,072
But I know my aunt lives
near the guest house.

215
00:15:48,155 --> 00:15:50,950
Are you staying at her place?
Until when, the weekend?

216
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:54,078
Yeah, but you know what…

217
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:56,455
I still can't come.

218
00:15:56,538 --> 00:16:01,251
How come? You're already nearby.
Just come and hang out with us, please?

219
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:02,503
Well…

220
00:16:04,713 --> 00:16:06,173
Would you know if Jae-eon is coming?

221
00:16:06,256 --> 00:16:10,427
Huh? No, I think he said
he had other plans.

222
00:16:10,511 --> 00:16:12,012
Oh, I see.

223
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,848
I'll try dropping by if I have time.

224
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:17,726
But I'd appreciate it
if you don't tell anyone I'm here.

225
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:19,728
I won't. My lips are sealed.

226
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:21,814
Just don't ignore my calls anymore.

227
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:24,525
Okay, great. It's a deal. Bye!

228
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:30,322
But didn't Jae-eon tell everyone
that he was coming, too?

229
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:32,533
-Yeah, he did.
-Then why did you lie?

230
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:35,160
Oh, my god. Did I really?

231
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:38,414
Whatever. I had to say that
to get Na-bi to change her mind.

232
00:16:39,915 --> 00:16:41,500
I think you're just begging for trouble.

233
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:44,837
No way, it would be awesome
if they get back together because of us.

234
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,005
"Us"?

235
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:47,840
You're on your own.
Don't drag me into this.

236
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:50,759
But you're here and you heard everything,
so you don't have a choice.

237
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,928
She doesn't even like the guy, you know?

238
00:16:53,929 --> 00:16:55,681
Yeah, I know that.

239
00:16:55,764 --> 00:16:57,808
But seriously, when she asked me
if he was coming,

240
00:16:57,891 --> 00:17:00,102
it sounded like
she really wanted him to be there.

241
00:17:00,644 --> 00:17:02,730
But don't you dare tell Na-bi
that I said that, okay?

242
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:04,231
That's between us.

243
00:17:04,314 --> 00:17:06,775
-All right.
-So, you wanna see a movie?

244
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:08,527
I have plans today.

245
00:17:08,610 --> 00:17:12,114
Huh? What plans?
With whom? You didn't tell me.

246
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:14,283
With Se-hun. He just asked me to lunch.

247
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:16,869
I wonder what he's up to this time?

248
00:17:16,952 --> 00:17:19,413
Well, nothing, I'm sure.

249
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:22,374
He just said something
about… asking help for work.

250
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:24,168
And a phone call can't do that?

